## Hints for Future Agents
- libsqlite3-dev in CI is for compiling `pysqlite3` (source-only on PyPI) for the
  langchain shard's chromadb. Removing it WILL likely break the langchain shard's
  dependency build. The clean fix to keep it green is `pysqlite3` ->
  `pysqlite3-binary` (bundles its own sqlite) in pyproject's langchain group;
  user explicitly scoped that dep change OUT for now ("not that").
- dependabot.yml still has `pysqlite3*` under the `langchain` group (untouched).
- The step ran for ALL ~25 shards in test.yaml (not gated to langchain) — was
  wasteful even before removal.

## Codebase Discoveries
- Trace-server backends are now exactly clickhouse (default) + fake in-memory;
  `--trace-server` help text confirms. The old sqlite trace server used stdlib
  `sqlite3`, so it required no CI apt package — nothing CI-side was its remnant.
- tests/trace/test_client_trace.py:4441 `clickhouse_client` fixture returns None
  on the fake backend (find_server_layer(..., ClickHouseTraceServer) raises
  TypeError) — that's what the stale "sqlite clients" skip was really gating.

